gurmukhi: cVY pwn bwnI Dry swn mwno cCw bwn sohY doaU rwm rwnI ]
transliteration: Chadai Paan Baaniddare Saan Maano Chachhaadbaan Sohai Dooo Raam Raanee||
translation: Ram looks glorious with the sharp arrows in his hands and Sita, the queen of Ram appears elegant with the beautiful arrows of her eyes.

gurmukhi: iPrY iKAwl so eyk hvwl syqI Cuty ieMdR syqI mno ieMdR DwnI ]
transliteration: Phirai Khiaal So Ek Havaal Setichhoute Indra Setimano Indra Dhaanee||
translation: She roams with Ram, being absorbed into such thoughts as if having been ousted from his capital Indra was staggering hither and thither.

gurmukhi: mno nwg bwNky ljI Awb PwNkY rMgy rMg suhwb sO rwm bwry ]
transliteration: Mano Naag Baanke Lajiaab Phaanke Rane Ran Suhaab Sou Raam Bhare||
translation: The loose hair of her braids, causing shyness to the glory of nagas, are becoming a sacrifice to Ram.

gurmukhi: miRgw dyiK mohy lKy mIn rohy ijnY nYk cIny iqnO pRwn vwry ]297]
transliteration: Mrigad Dekh(i) Mohe Lakhe Meen Rohe Jinai Naik Cheene Tinau Praan Vdare||297||
translation: The deers looking at her are allured by her, the fishes looking at her beauty are feeling jealous of her; he, whoever had seen her, had sacrified himself for her.297.

gurmukhi: suny kUk ky koklw kop kIny muKM dyK kY cMd dwry rKweI ]
transliteration: Soune Kook Ke Kokalaa Kop Keene Moukhannddekh Kai Channd Ddare Rakhaaee||
translation: The nightingale, listening to her speech, is getting angry on account of jealousy and the moon looking at her face is feeling shy like women,

gurmukhi: lKy nYn bwNky mnY mIn mohY lKy log BUly bny jor AYsy ]
transliteration: Lakhe Nain Baanke Manai Meen Mohair Lakhe Jaat Ke Soor Kijot(i) Chhaade||
translation: The fish is allured by seeing her eyes and her beauty seems like the extension of sunlight.

gurmukhi: mno PUl PUly lgy nYn JUly lKy log BUly bny jor AYsy ]
transliteration: Mano Phool Phoole Lage Nain Jhoole Lakhe Log Bhoole Bade Jor Aise||
translation: Seeing her eyes they appear like the blossomed lotus and all the people in the forest are extremely enchanted by her beauty.

gurmukhi: lKy nYn Qwry ibDy rwm ipAwry rMgy rMg swrwb suhwb jYsy ]298]
transliteration: Lakhe Nain Thdare Bidhe Raam Pidare Rane Ran Saaraab Suhaab Jaise||298||
translation: O Sita ! seeing your intoxicated eyes Ram himself seems pierced by them.298.

gurmukhi: rMgy rMg rwqy mXM m`q mwqy mkbUil gu`lwb ky PUl sohYN ]
transliteration: Rane Ran Raate Moyan Matt Maate Makbool(i) Gullaab Ke Phool Sohain||
translation: Your eyes are intoxicated, having been dyed in your love and it seems that they are lovely roses.

gurmukhi: nrgs ny dyKkY nwk AYNTw miRgIrwj ky dyKqYN mwn mohYN ]
transliteration: Nargad Ne Dekhkai Naak Ainthaa Mrigeeraaj Ke Dekhtain Maan Mohain||
translation: The narcissus flowers are expressing contempt with jealousy and the does on seeing her are feeling blow at their self-respect,

gurmukhi: sbo roj srwb ny sor lwieAw pRjw Awm jwhwn ky pyK vwry ]
transliteration: Sabo Roj Saraab Ne Sor Laaiaa Prajaa Aam Jaahaan Ke Pekh Vdare||
translation: The wine in spite of all its strength is not feeling itself equivalent to thhe ardent passion of Sita in the whole world,

gurmukhi: Bvw qwn kmwn kI BwNq ipAwrI in kmwn hI nYn ky bwn mwry ]299]
transliteration: Bhavaa Taan Kamaan Kibhaant Piaarini Kamaan Hi Nain Ke Baan Mdare||299||
translation: Her eyebrows are lovely like the bow and from those eyebrows she is discharging the arrows of her eyes.299.
